result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (2nd Offense)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (2nd Offense)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Philip T Dzibinski was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Philip T Dzibinski in court with attorney Mark D. Lawton.  Troy D Cross appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Cases heard: 15CM463 & 16CM241.  Defendant pleads no contest   to count 1 in 16CM241 & 15CM463.  Court will adjudge guilty of count 1 in  both cases and enter JOC and dismiss all other counts in both cases.  Court imposes in 16CM241: ct 1: 5 days in jail with huber to begin  today at 7:00 pm, $1379.00 due 60 days or pay plan, 12 month revocation & IID upon licensure, AODA & treatment, DNA Sample to be submitted.  Court imposes in 15CM463 ct 1 amended to OWI-3rd: 240 days jail with huber but stayed and defendant to complete OWI treatment court.  2 years probation with conds:  24 days jail with huber-no good time consecutive to 5 days in 16CM241, $2452.00, $65.00 Poynette blood draw, 24 month revocation & IID upon licensure, AODA & treatment, not possess/consume alcohol, DNA sample to be submitted.  3 days jail credit in 15CM463.  0 days on 16CM241.  Civil traffics talked after hearing was completed.  They are to be dismissed.
Copy of Letter from ADA Troy Cross to Atty Mark Lawton   re:  Discovery.
Plea/sentencing hearing on May 26, 2016 at 11:30 am.

ADA Troy Cross appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant appeared in person with Atty Mark Lawton.  16CM241 filed.  Sentencing recommendations; will argue jail length.    Discussion regarding resetting both cases as defendant interested in OWI Treatment Court but needs to see what that involves.  Court adjourns 15CM463.  In 16CM241, reading waived, attorney rights.  Advised defendant he must take steps to get Atty Lawton to represent in this case.  ADA Cross not opposed to signature bond.  Court imposed $2500 signature bond with conditions:  Not operate MV without valid DL, not to go upon premises for on site consumption, maintain absolute sobriety.  Jury trial remains on calendar.  Atty Lawton to contact court before trial date.
